The **eleventh season** of the [American](/wiki/United_States "United States")
[reality television](/wiki/Reality_television "Reality television") series
_**[Food Network Star](/wiki/Food_Network_Star "Food Network Star")**_
premiered June 7, 2015 on [Food Network](/wiki/Food_Network "Food
Network").[1] Food Network [chefs](/wiki/Chef "Chef") [Bobby
Flay](/wiki/Bobby_Flay "Bobby Flay") and [Giada de
Laurentiis](/wiki/Giada_de_Laurentiis "Giada de Laurentiis") returned to the
series as [judges](/wiki/Adjudicator "Adjudicator"), with [Alton
Brown](/wiki/Alton_Brown "Alton Brown") not returning for undisclosed
reasons.[2] This season also continued the inclusion of _Star Salvation_ , a
six-week[3] [webseries](/wiki/Web_series "Web series") that featured the most
recently eliminated contestant competing against the remaining previously
eliminated contestants for a chance to re-enter the main _Food Network Star_
competition.

This season also returned to the practice of the winner of the competition
being chosen by the Food Network staff, rather than [by
viewers](/wiki/Opinion_poll "Opinion poll") as in the three previous
seasons.[4]
